== Head-to-head record ==
{{Main|Canada men's national football team head-to-head record}}
As of June 5, 2026, the complete official match record of the Canada men's national team comprises 476 matches: 179 wins, 112 draws and 185 losses.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.11v11.com/teams/canada/tab/stats/|title=Canada national football team statistics and records: All-time record|publisher=11v11.com}}</ref> During these matches, the team scored 606 times and conceded 597 goals. Canada's highest winning margin is 11 goals, which was achieved against the [[Cayman Islands national football team|Cayman Islands]] in 2021 (11–0).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbc.ca/sports/soccer/soccer-canada-cayman-islands-recap-march-29-qatar-2022-1.5968970|title=Canadian men set scoring record, crushing Cayman Islands 11-0 in World Cup qualifier|publisher=cbc.ca|date=March 29, 2021}}</ref> Their longest winning streak is eight wins,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/soccer/article-canada-defeats-depleted-haiti-4-1-at-gold-cup/|title=Canada defeats depleted Haiti 4-1 at Gold Cup|publisher=theglobeandmail.com|date=July 15, 2021}}</ref> and their unbeaten record is 15 consecutive official matches.

